   <mods:abstract>Kenneth Rendell Catalog # 45 (1970), item 156. Autograph Letter signed, 5
            1/2 p. Docketed by Jay. Printed in full (based on this manuscript version in Syrett,
            ed., Hamilton, vol. 2:189-192. Reply to Jay's letter of 18 September. Shares Jay's
            reservations about William Malcom. Clarifies his remarks on Neuville. Thanks Jay for his
            work on behalf of Fleury. Discusses Colombe's commission and the general question of
            brevet appointments. Reports on sightings of ships.</mods:abstract>
